caption: Delicious food and excellent service.
the place is awesome and even their food too
Delicious food, comfortable environment

Great food and awesome service. I had pork belly barbecue, seafood pajeon (my favourite), and kimchi dumplings. All three of these dishes were really good. This was shared by two people and we were totally full. Good date spot as well.
Fully enjoyed time spent here. Food is quite excellent. First KBBQ experience was a total win.
Decent Korean BBQ and very much worth the visit over K-town. Fried chicken was very tender and juicy, though the sauce was a little too sweet for my taste.
Really a well taken care of resteraunt. I have seen few kitchens as clean as theirs. Will definitely be going back.
The place serves large dishes and for convenient pricing. very nice staff members. Kudos.
You can simply not go wrong with this fine dining institution. Currently open with few tables to enable distancing.
Good food. The restaurant week pasta was amazing .
it was good.  food ok .service excellent. I would recommend pancakes and fried chicken.. BBQ not worth it .. just my opinion.. pineapple jalapeños ice cream very recommend!!!

We got No Curfew cocktails which had coffee liqueur! Innovative cocktails for sure. For food, we got Ojingeo Twigim and Jjajhang Saewoo. Both of the dishes were absolutely delicious. Also loved all the banchan included. Perfect place of Korean BBQ for a group.

We met with friends at this restaurant for dinner. my friend recommended this restaurant.  Well, it was very successful. the staff members were so friendly and we felt good. The meal was yummy. We enjoyed every moment and we shall absolutely come back again. we highly recommend this place.
One of my go-to spots to grab some food. great location, well kept, and awesome service. A must try!
Nice place

Cool vibe, attentive service and yummy food. The vegetarian bibimbap is very tasty (be sure to order it in the hot clay pot). Cocktails were also a treat. It’s a little more expensive in comparison to other local restaurants of the same quality but would recommend!
Hubby took me for birthday, didn't care for it to much..... Was looking for more authentic Korean BBQ.....

Excellent location for korean bbq. Service is always awesome even when they have a full house. The service here is attentive. It has an awesome feel to it. I see why this place has so many great reviews.
Good food and service.
Dinning out is not a good experience. But food is pretty good. A little bit too expensive.

Great Korean spot, but pricey to the point where it really is not worth to do the bbq table experience (unless you are taking someone who has never done anything like it before). The move here is to eat in the bar area and order off the normal menu, which is amazing and a much much better deal than the bbq. Great tiki style cocktails as well. Only 4 stars because of the expense and the bbq side will rope people in when it is not what shines here.

I meet friends in this lovely place many times a year! This is my favorite spot to eat.  I visit this spot regularly. The cooking is very good, the workers are helpful and the charge is affordable. I enjoy going in this spot to have a nice supper.

Occasion : my friend's B-day dinner. Group of 10. The decor here is very sleek and minimalist. Festive atmosphere. The place insisted that all of us be there for our 8:30pm reservation. Few of us hanged out by the bar. When the time came, they were still able to sit us minus one person.  Drinks:  The most impressive cocktail was the Jade Emperor (we got 4 of them) It was made from Pisco, matcha (not a strong flavor) with a strong cucumber taste. Very refreshing! Eastern Lights were also a hit for those preferring to drink vodka.  Food: We were confused at first about how to proceed. All credit goes to our server Justin who guided each of us with our choices. We all ordered an item for BBQ and shared family style. Food was made tableside with accompanied side dishes. He gave good suggestions. Here is what we loved from the menu:  -THE RIBEYE. It ran for $45. But it was so flavorful, so tender. -Beef Tartare. Surprisingly so so delicious! Probably my favorite dish -Yangnyum Galbi. Beef short rib. A good option after the rib, had a BBQ flavor. -Dolsot Bibimbap with bulgogi. Came in a good portion! -Japchae. Loved the glass noodles! -Samgyeopsal. thinly sliced pork belly. looked like bacon. still good!  Cons: the biggest cons is obviously the price. Our bill came down to a whopping $596. And it's not like I walked out of there with a super full belly. Obviously not an everyday type of place to eat.
This spot is awesome! Affordable prices, considerable portions and the staff are consistently nice.
We had a fantastic  at this restaurant. We liked the awesome ambience and the menu. The staff members were very personal. I’m glad we finally managed to visit this spot.
Solid Korean bbq

The perfect date: Go to the bar and order the Scorpion bowl + a half a Korean fried chicken. Get there around 6pm before it gets jumping. Grab two seats at the bar.  Relax.  Enjoy.  My wife and I have been doing this for the past two years on Friday nights. Joy.
This place nailed it for a quaran-tuesday dinner. Please support local restaurants and order pick up or delivery meals. Highly recommend Insa.
Great service and food
Good setting/location, but food was not great/worth it kbbq wise.
Best Karaoke!!! Also the food is on point.
Great food drinks and karaoke!  Giving 3 stars because the food isn't the best...

Love the karaoke bar but the food not so much. The brisket is dry and doesn't taste good at all, dumplings taste like overcooked egg rolls... The only good thing on the menu are the cocktails.  So if you want to have a drink and sing your heart away... This is the place to be!

The service was great, the environment was the best among all korean restaurants I've visited in the U.S.  However, this is not the taste in Korea. We don't eat these tasting food in Korea, especially fried chicken.

My mother is from Korea and another Asian friend also came for dinner.  Both are well acquainted with Korean food.  The appetizer dishes were old.  The potatoe salad was good.  The Kalbi meet was fresh and the bulgogi was also good but the rice wasn't cooked enough.  Most Americans won't notice the difference.   If you want good Kimchi and related, this isnt the place.  Atmosphere was nice, good service and clean Premise.

Very good Korean bbq spot. While alil on the pricey side, I’ve eaten here 2/3 times and the quality is consistently excellent. Whether ordering meats for the grill, or regular dishes, it’s all great. Come with a group of friends, stuff yourselves & then rent a private karaoke room in the back and have a ball. You won’t regret it.

Tasty food and nice ambiance, but pretty expensive for what you get. Prices were originally high because they were proud to say that they were a no tip restaurant, but that is no longer a thing. So generally not affordable for everyone.
Really fun. Little loud if that's not your jam, but great experience
Great service, great food, incredibly well run and friendly staff and high quality food ingredients.  Had a great time last night celebrating my wife’s birthday, thank you Insa staff!

This place is my number one site.  Of all restaurants I know I like it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to visit this restaurant. everytime  I want to go to a superb lunchon, this is the place that comes straight to my mind. exeptionalgorgeous and many types of  food and a large list of dishes.helpful team, and nice vibes. And very important, the pay is good. I sent my friends to this restaurant with pleasure.

We ordered a couple variations of pork and was very impressed, very tender and flavorful. Prices are at the higher range but the quality is definitely there. The service staff was very friendly and accommodating too.

They use your table grill to cook the food for you. Food is good but not amazing. Definitely enjoyed the karaoke section, had so much fun. Cocktails were great but the bar area gets crowded pretty quickly and becomes inconvenient to stand out sometimes sit.

This place is worth the trip deep into Brooklyn.  The food is plenty and filing.  If you are not a seafood lover you will be ok with plenty of good beef and chicken options as well.  The wait staff is very friendly.  We did karaoke as well and that was a great experience.  There is an app where you can find and select songs....saves you from flipping through the song book....but they have books as well.
First visit; clean, friendly and good food
Awesome dishes, and a very friendly atmosphere but service varies...
Poor ad placement. Not going

Four of us came without a reservation & the host wanted us to wait for 45 mins even though there are at least three communal tables without anyone on it. While we convened, another came by and offered a table if we can finish our meal in 1.5 hours. Duh, yes! No one should eat that long in Brooklyn 😆 Our server is great, patience and gave us good tips on portion and dishes to order. We got the squid/octopus bbq and pancetta coreana bbq (all of them are delicious especially the pork belly which are oozing with wonderful lard), japchae (full of flavor) and the kimchi fried rice with bacon (I don’t really like Kim chi but this fried rice is crispy lips smacking). Overall is a great experience and dinner but I do wish the portion can be larger especially the bbq dishes given the prices.

Last week was the first time we visited this magnificent restaurant. But It is absolutely not the last time. We had a good time with the courteous service, with the great  food and booze and with the friendly payment. We will surely return there in a short time.

Wow, capitalism sings a sad song. Booked a reservation for 12 people for a holiday party for 12/11/19 (confirmed on 11/14/19), we had some of our team from California flying out just for the party. They called me on the night of 11/25/19 at 9:15PM probably hoping I wouldn't answer, to tell me they had someone who wanted to do a buyout of the entire restaurant so they had to cancel our reservation. As a fellow business owner, I can't imagine a worse example of customer service.  The worst part is that I found out from a friend that it was their company that did the buy-out and I know that they requested to do the buy-out the day that they canceled my reservation. Meaning a better opportunity came along and the restaurant decided it was a better fiscal decision to screw over all the other reservation holders so they could make a couple of extra bucks.  #sad
Service fine but the food qualify very poor
Decent Korean food place near the cobble Hill area. Crowded on the weekends. It's not a full fledge BBQ place like other Korean BBQ resturant. Good place but not on par with any place in Korea Town..
Best chicken in the world
Amazing fried chicken, Bib Bim bap, and cocktails. Such a friendly staff willing to go above and beyond. What a gem in BK!
I'm pescatarian.  I ordered vegetable dumplings but was given dumplings with pork & beef.  Casual place with comfortable bar seating.  Music is very loud.
Overpriced and the food isn’t worth it. Service was neglectful and a bit rude.

This place was incredible! The servers were really nice and helpful! I typically hate Korean Barbeque but this was really refined-- maybe it's because other ppl ordered everything and they know what to do.

We met with friends at this spot for a meeting. This restaurant was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, we were not disappointed. The staff welcomed us with a smile and we felt very good. The food was just great. We enjoyed every moment and we will visit this place again. Keep it up.
Food and tableside service were amazing.
A nice Korean restaurant with astronomical prices. Do yourself a favor and explore Korean town or better yet, head to Queens. Cheers all!
No better place to get fresh and authentic Korean food. Had an amazing time!
The customer service is always swift, lovely mood, kind staff members. Will visit here again when I get in the area.
We were impressed by the tasteful decor, cordial and well informed service and particularly the delicious food with tastes ranging from robust to delicate. Interesting drinks selection too.
Loved it, nice atmosphere, lots of delicious appetizers. Service is okay, $$ for prices, but it worth it.
The karaoke was nice, but the food I dont reccomend
I always arrive buying some food here. I enjoy the swift customer service and well prepared dishes. They never disappoint.
We had an excellent experience at this place. We enjoyed the excellent environment and the meals. The staff were very attentive. I’m content we finally decided to try this place.
I actually loved their food and service, awesome location next to my house. The cashiers are always nice. Will come back again.
Their chicken is amazing.  Had a wonderful time doing karaoke. The set up is great.  Will go again
Tried this spot already with my friend and I am hooked ever since. I liked the awesome ambience and yummy dishes and drinks. Highly recommended.
The place serves big portions and for affordable prices. kind staff members. Never disappointing.
Good food. Ktv way overpriced, song selection and system dated

One of the best Korean BBQ places in Brooklyn. Don't let the front door phase you, the place is huge on the inside. One giant hall with several private rooms for parties and kareoke.  The food is delicious, and very good beverage menu. The staff is fast and courteous, and chefs know their stuff.
Excellent warm and friendly service. Great cocktails and delicious consistent food.
Great Korean and karaoke

Very good traditional style KBBQ in a not very traditional setting. Love the decor and size of the space. Food is very solid and staff is very attentive and helpful. Would recommend for KBBQ if you're not around more traditional spots.
Fernando was the most amazing help and support between dinner and our karaoke groups for out of state groups. We will sure to be back. Thank you!
Very much worth the price. Try the Mai Tai.
The food is constantly well prepared and flavorful, employees hands over fantastic service. I really like how neat it is and vibes. Would recommend to others.
Very tasty, good service, but veryx2 expensive.
Great and delicious food, I loved the ambience this place has, and the employees were welcoming. Will surely come back again.
Bar, bbq, ktv. Beers are mostly Japanese though.
Great selection of food with good prices. They also had a good drink menu.
I visit this spot a lot since I work nearby. I must say their customer service is always great and they keep the place well kept at all times. Pricing is convenient and they serve big portions.
Bibimbap was perfectly crispy on the bottom and the sweet potato noodles and house made spam were delicious😍. I will definitely visit again!

A very okay Korean BBQ. The fried chicken was delicious, but after that it wasn't much to talk about. The staff is great and the design is lovely, but the BBQ portion left much to be desired. It wasn't worth it to me personally, I will most likely not be coming back.

I ate here with my husband and ordered samgyebsal(BBQ pork belly), kimchi fried rice, and Jjolmyun. Kimchi fried rice was way too greasy and pork belly was one of the worst i ever had. It was little bit sour which is I don’t understand why. And strange thing about this place was they didn’t serve any dipping sauce for pork belly BBQ. Well, Jjolmyun was only ok from here. All the side dishes were bad too except for that black beans.
The food is great and there is a comfortable bar as well. But there is one waitress that's rude about tips.
Food was good but a bit pricey. Staff were great - friendly and attentive, including the bartender!  They have karaoke too.
Would definitely recommend visiting this place. Great atmosphere, delicious food, good service. Keep up the good work.
Nice space. Nonchalant servers. Overpriced for the quality and quantity. But not bad.
The place serves big dishes and for fair prices. very nice owner. Kudos.

For the price, we expected the food to be flavorful and the service to be great. This restaurant has the prices of an upscale restaurant, but honestly, I've had much better food and service at casual Korean barbecue restaurants. The twice fried chicken was the best, but most of the barbecued meat (each around $30-50) was unseasoned and not as much to share as expected. Service was the worst. The servers are kind, but understaffed. The bartender was completely neglectful and we often were waiting upwards to 45 minutes for a beer and would have to go chase down the server to ask again. Overall, I'd say save your money and eat at a casual Korean barbecue place. Food will be the same, or better.
Lots of fun!!
Love the layout. And my BBQ ? Well I didn't have to cook it. I'm a fan.

We had a reservation for 8 for eating in the dining area, and then karaoke afterward. They have a tiki style bar area that we waited at for rest of our party to show up, as they don't seat until you have your full party.  After being seated and server came to take our order, a few subtle things started to happen. The server proceeded to walk away to attend to another table, halfway when we were making our order and deciding between items.  We ordered their house soju and they gave us a bottle that was 3 quarters finished. We let them know and they didn't even realize and were confused why we wanted to return the bottle, and we had to point it out more clearly to them. Then a different server came by and asked whether there was a problem with the bottle. We were surprised that there was such a lack of communication between the staff, it's clear that it was already drank by a different group before us. We haven't even started eating or drinking yet..  The poor service continued as they gave us an order for a different table. We had to correct them again.  In the end we tried to appreciate the food and drink, but their house made soju was actually disgusting. I'm not really sure what we expected, especially since it wasn't flavored soju or anything.  The meat quality was mediocre. We soon realized that the only reason why people came to this establishment was that they probably live too far from ktown manhanttan - because the price was the same for subpar meat quality.  I highly recommend against coming here if you are able to just go to ktown. This place also requires advanced reservation for weekend nights, I guess since it'd the only kbbq in the entire area.  The karaoke was decent. They have an app you can use for song selection.  Overall I would say if you live in bklyn it's probably an okay choice, but not worth trekking to if you're coming from Manhattan.

They have karaoke in the back and the setup is great. Experienced two of the rooms. One fit 8-10 and the other 20 or more. Good acoustics, several mics, a mini stage in the bigger room and a tambourine!
I now know which is the place that about to see a lot of me this year. Lived everything about Insa. Read reviews before, and now know they are true. Good food lovely place and great vibe. I loved it.
Tasteless
Came for a fun work event. Food & drinks were good. White wine bottle ordered not so great. Over all the experience was great and we would definitely come again to eat 1st then sing after.
The food didn't really wow me. However some of the dishes like the fish and the dumplings were good.
A wonderful experience. I forgot how much fun karaoke is. Hanging with friends, good food, service. Will come back and would highly recommend a visit to Insa.

First time at this place and the food was delicious. The staff was courteous and attentive. The appetizers, soup, rice, and noodles are all served fully cooked. The BBQ items are cooked at the table and served family style at the table. Our server Justin was attuned to our needs and overall he provided a great dinner service.

If you're looking at the reviews wondering whether their sterling reputation is well-deserved than look no further friend. I could find no fault in my dining experience from start to finish, the service was impeccable and amiable. The decor and atmosphere yielded a wonderful experience. A word to the wise though Insa gets busy and quick so come in early or make a reservation if you don't want to wait. But wait you're telling yourself any well-known restaurant will surely cost a pretty penny, worry not the serving sizes are rather large, an appetizer, entree and 2 drinks cost us a mere 40$ a person, making this outing a go to spot for a night out with the fellas. Perfect for dates, celebrations or just to grab dinner at. Finally the food, my god the food was amazing! The reputation of their fried chicken is in-fact understated in my opinion one of the crispiest and most flavorful eats I've had in NYC. Now the BBQ is an absolute blast, the meat is good quality and the Ssam style is so much fun. Seriously get off of google maps and go eat you will not regret it!
Had a great night hanging out at the bat. The food was great and the drinks were tasty. Shout out to Ryan for being a great bartender and all around cool guy.
meh
Fun karaoke, and good Korean BBQ. Staff is friendly as well.
Really great food nom nom. The karaoke is great too (it's half off mon-tue-wed ;) wasn't me who told you)

My wife and I asked for a separate check from our party since we were leaving before karaoke at the start of the meal. The waitress told us we coiuld  get a separate check. When the check came at the end of the meal it was all one check when we got a separate check after arguing they hit my wife and I with a twenty percent gratuity. I would never return to this place. The service was awful and the waitress lied to our face repeatedly. If you want good service look elsewhere. The manegment was also completely incompetent and unhelpful.
LOVE everything about this restaurant- the menu, the wings, the karaoke rooms etc.
Be prepared to spend your hard earned cash on food that is just plain mediocre. It's like Korean BBQ wannabes. Go to Korean town in the city. You will be better off.
#porkmafia inda house

Really bad food with not much taste and little accommodation for vegetarians except for a few dishes on a separate menu. Even the banchan were not very good. All four people ended up not eating most of the food because it tasted so bad. Also very overpriced -- paid about $100 for rice topped with some chopped vegetables.
Over priced Korean BBQ. You're paying for the convenience of having  karaoke rooms in a restaurant. The food is well below average. Go for a good group setting, not for the food.

Best cocktails. Food is delicious. Service is always good.
Food tasted great. But it's as the other reviews have said the food price is a little higher than I'd like.

We did karaoke first. We were a party of like 12 people, so we ended up squished at one of the longer tables. At one point during the meal we ask to change the grill since it was a bit burnt and the girl (think she was new) looked at us like we had multiple heads. The other waitress who was our main server sorted things out. Food was just ok, more like knock of Korean BBQ. If you’re wondering when the vents are... they’re under the tables. 😉

Very delicious Korean BBQ Spacious and lively atmosphere Clean restaurant and restrooms Karaoke rooms available  My only concern was getting our fried rice and noodles towards the end. We would’ve preferred to have them in the beginning or with the meat at least.  Yangnyum Galbi (Beef Short Rib) 👍🏼 Insa Fried Chicken 👍🏼 Kkot Deungshim (Dry Aged Ribeye)👎🏼
Had better service before

Long wait. Called and hostess said 20 min wait. Didn't let us put our names down. When we arrived 5 mins later, the wait became 1-1.5 hours! That's a huge difference! They should just allow reservations over then phone or last least allow people to put their names down over the phone. What's the point of making people come in to put their names down just so they could go to other neighborhood restaurants when the wait is long!? The business model is unsound and needs flexibility, especially in a digital age like today.
(Translated by Google) Very good food and prices. The place is nice and has karaoke rooms.  (Original) Muy buena comida y precios. El lugar es bonito y tiene habitaciones de karaoke.
It was okay. Seemed too pricey for what we paid for. For 29 dollars I had 3 slices of meat which was not enough for 2 people. There was almost no meet in soup for 17 dollars.

Came here on a date last night. It was the two of us on a Sunday night at 6:30. The wait was 45 minutes (They don't take reservations!) BUT they were very kind to inform us they had service at the bar.  I excitedly jumped at the chance. When you first walk in, there's a little window that peaks into the bar/lounge area -- it's red, lush, and visually my aesthetic.  There were a few seats at the side bar, but we were so crazy lucky there was an entire BOOTH open! It feel like a dream, we had skipped the whole line and found this hidden gem. So if it's crowded when you go, seriously see if you can swap to the bar. We skipped a group of five that could have easily fit in the booth.  The bar area is waiterless, but the bar is 2 steps away and the food is delivered to you anyway.  We had the gogi mandu fried, tteokbokki, and bossam.  My favourite was the Gogi Mandu, amazing flavour and just the right level of crispy. Everything was great too. It was nice to go out and enjoy every aspect of the night.  Our cocktails were fabulous, I recommend the Sun&Moon.  It's worth the trek if you're not from the neighbourhood. I would love to come back.
(Translated by Google) Delicious gal bi  (Original) Delicious gal bi
The food here is so good. The staff has stellar recommendations and is very personable. The barbecue is absolutely delicious. The beef, the pork, and the octopus were amazing!
Absolutely fantastic Korean food and wonderful service.

This place has potential but overall has too many problems and we left disappointed.  The space is great with tall ceilings and good ambience. The servers are nice enough. They do grill and cut the food at your table. We came with a party of 5. The wait was an hour, so we went across the street to the bar. After 90 minutes we called and the hostess said they had tried calling but it was the wrong number. Okay.. we let that pass and came back for our table. We ordered 3 items from the BBQ section plus an order of pajeon which was the amount the server recommended. The food was tasty but we all left unsatisfied. An order or kalbi is only 2 or 3 pieces for $30. The rice came out halfway through our meal. The banchan (sides) were small and we had to ask for refills. Some of the sides we didn’t get refills on even after asking. Eventually we just ate the meat and rice before it got cold.

So, we went there yesterday, super excited about grilling the meat etc. The interior is stunning. The manu very pricey. We ordered fried rice with spam, fish and brisket bbq. Now, the fish was amazing, the rice was great but very plain. Not much flavour. The reason i gave it two stars is because of those two dishes. However, theBBQ was a disaster. The meat was so thin that the waiter who grilled it overcooked it and it was the most chewiest meat I have ever had! Not only it wasn’t seasoned. But the flavour was horrible. I couldn’t eat it, we leftmost of it on the plate- no oneasked us if it was ok. We left with $116 bill for a less than avarage meal. Won’t becoming back. Shame because I live so close and the interior isstunning. Please work onyour menu and maybe serve good quality meat.

Despite the fact of already passed hype of asian everything aand korean bars they have not manged to made decent menu or prepare food. Go to korea town and go there to have the same dish and youll see - very vey weak. And for that price- c'mon! But it's one of few places in that overrated city that looks and have the feeling of restaurant ambience, not a dirty hole.
Amazing, KBBQ. Beautiful interior space. Good for larger parties and groups. I come here when I wanna treat myself. This place is fancier than some of the AYCE places.
Great food
Great food, karaoke and drinks
Remember that scene where we find out Emma Stone is somewhat Asian in the movie Aloha? Here’s the the restaurant version. The movie has 20% on Rotten Tomatoes.

I'm sorry, didn't hit the mark.  A big fan of Korean BBQ, I was left sadden by the experience.  The food unfortunately was a muted version of the typical Korean spread and the service suffered as well.  Wish we would have taken our $$$ to flushing.
great food and good portions.
Great Korean BBQ
Great food, great atmosphere. Happened to go on a rainy day, so the wait wasn't ludicrous.
Great food and service, though slightly on the more expensive side.
I find them serving super authentic Korean food just like what I’ve had in Korea. Everything is cooked deliciously and served hot. Price is fair too.
Love it. A must if you want to try something new
Loved it
Hidden little secret

If you are Korean, don't go there. I could not feel any Korean from the food. BTW we ordered jabchae, crab maewoontang, and pork mandoo. We had to return the crab Tang since it had plastic lines in it. Other two are mediocre. Side dishes are not tasty either. The last stop of a short NY trip was not a success.
Tried the grill food. It’s over charred and leaves a burnt taste in mouth. Yuck!
great food and cocktails
Really fun atmosphere, great cocktails, and awesome food! Fried chicken was amazing!! Def recommend!!  PS well ventilated so you won’t smell like the bbq after your meal!!
Poor quality of food... It's not a real korean food. It didn't seem staffs understood what Korean food is.

Always solid. If it's a busy night you can sometimes get lucky with bar seats or a bigger bar table. We love the chicken, the rice cakes, the seafood pancake. Great with a group. Call ahead and make a reservation for after dinner to sing karaoke.
its alright
Great food..staff was really nice and helpful

Unique Korean food experience with the coolest cozy kareoke rooms. The chicken was incredible, juicy, crispy, spicy and so flavorful! The clear noodles were fresh and full of good veggies and the dumplings had the perfect texture. The beer selection was super with tons of local brew options, they even had a beer that's made across the street. Of course I can't forget to mention they have Korean beers like OB and HITE. The place is suitable for any occasion.

Amazing space for a one stop party shop. Dope bar, huge restaurant space with tableside Korean BBQ, perfect for large groups, and even karaoke rooms! The food is amazing. Highlights were the seafood corndog and the army stew which has their delicious homemade spam.

The aged ribeye was fantastic, highly recommend that option and cooking it yourself to tinker with perfection. The fried chicken was pretty good too. They add gratuity automatically to checks and do not expect tips. Finally!

Really enjoyed coming to Insa for dinner with a group of friends and karaoke afterwards. Quality of the food was excellent with the price cheaper than what you would get in Ktown. I liked the bibimbap and Korean fried chicken (must come back for maekju). However, our server was not very polite so I cannot give the full five stars.

Very nice casual atmosphere good for large groups or couple's. BEWARE If you have SHELLFISH allergy. Almost every dish contains shellfish but they have a separate little menu for you but it's not much on it. Strong drinks and very pricey.
The food here is very good and high quality. Overall the restaurant is pricey but it is worth it. They have seating that works for big or small groups.
Really liked the food. We had beef and seafood bbq options and thoroughly enjoyed it.  Only the wait for the table slightly ruined our experience. Will be back however!
Get the whole chicken.
Half-off the karaoke rooms M-W and the food is always so delicious!!

We did private room karaoke for two hours and had a BLAST...until the check came. This place is EXPENSIVE. We had a group of 9 people there for 2 hours this weekend, we split three small dishes and walked out each paying $100. Insane! My vote is to always go to K-Town for karaoke, but if you’re set on this place, you’ll have a good time. Just save up beforehand.
Loved the Kareoke rooms and great service!

Sad if this is anyone's intro to Korean BBQ. Food ranged from okay to good, but KO BBQ is normally a fast moving meal and that speed was lacking. Service was friendly but not very attentive or comfortable cooking the meat for us.
Great food great environment and I even got a free dish when I went. Pricing a little High, averaging around 16-18 dollars per dish.
Go for half price karaoke M - W

. After reading other reviews I felt I needed to edit my review that follows. We had no problem with that and tipped our waiter anyway which by the way he told us  wasn’t necessary. Would go back again today if I could.  First time trying Korean BBQ and I was not disappointed. One of the best meals of my life! The restaurant it self was very inviting with a view of the kitchen. Even the bathrooms were spotless which might not seem like a big thing but says a lot about the owner and staff. There’s a small but very cozy bar off the dining room with craft beer from the brewery across the street. The IPA was fantastic! Our waiter James did a great job of explaining and preparing the food at the table side BBQ. We were a group of 4 and even after tipping above the %20 that’s added to the bill so they can give the staff medical benefits which we had no problem with it was $100 per person. Considering how much we drank and ate I thought we definitely got our monies worth.

I was so excited to finally have some Korean barbecue, it had been months since I have had any. I'm originally from California and had been looking forever to find a new Korean barbecue place, and when I came across this restaurant I felt like this was the closest place I could find to back home. So, when the friendly Hostess greeted me I was uber excited to be there. But, then the waitress came and that's where it all went downhill. I told her I wanted to use the grill in front of me and that I would like some bulgogi and we briefly discussed what other food could be put on the grill, and we came to the conclusion  of me ordering the bulgogi she then placed my order, what took like it seemed forever to get to me. It turned out that they don't serve bulgogi Raw, it is cooked and is served to you that way. I was highly disappointed due to the fact that the only reason I went there was to use the grill to cook meat and have the total experience. This was something I told the hostess in excitement and my waitress. It quite frankly seems to me that the waitress just was not even really paying attention to anything I was saying and when my food got to me it turns out I was right. She, asked me if I would like a drink and I agreed that yes I would like another drink. After waiting 15 minutes with no drink to arrive, she then returned to me and said, "are we done, would you like your receipt?" I  couldn't help but look at her dumbfounded and think to myself, you haven't even checked on me at all! Now, that you see I'm done with my food, now you ask if I want to drink then when I say I do you don't even bring it, it seemed at the time she was avoiding me after I got my meal. Knowing that it wasn't the way I had originally requested it, and when she did bring me my food, and it came to me cook and I asked her why. She tried telling me that she told me I couldn't cook it on the grill, that was a complete lie. It's one thing to be served the wrong food, it's another thing for the waitress to then try to put it on you, that was absolutely not okay! Then you asked me for a drink and disappear again, finally you ask me for my receipt and act as if everything was okay. The lack of common sense that she used, really ruined my whole experience; for one having Korean barbecue for the first time in New York and two at this individual location. Then when I get my receipt not being advised that there is already a service fee that is going to be attached, the first thing I told my waitress when I sat down was that this was my first time eating Korean BBQ in New York and being at this restaurant, one would think she would have as a waitress, advise me of all of the ins and outs within their establishment from food to how they serve two prices. But, no none of this was even considered for my service. That infuriated me, because the service was one non-existent and two her communication was non-existent, so therefore requiring me to give a service fee for service that was not properly rendered, quite frankly was ridiculous. I will never come to this establishment again and since  I have  been here,  I have had people ask me about it and I tell them that it is their choice if they want to go or not, but I would never recommend it to anyone. The Ambiance was nice and to know that they had karaoke in the back was nice as well, but that didn't make up for the lack of customer service. The hostess could tell I was upset and tried to apologize as I walked out, but that was not her responsibility, I could see she was making a last-ditch effort to salvage what had gone South due to the waitress, the hostess had even said she could talk to the chef for me but once again that was not her responsibility.
